A4.text: In eukaryotes, NADH is the most important electron donor.

A5.text: In prokaryotes, there are several different electron donors.

A6.text: The mitochondrial NADH is then oxidized in turn by the electron transport chain

A7.text: In eukaryotes the electrons carried by the NADH that is produced in the cytoplasm are transferred into the mitochondrion (to reduce mitochondrial NAD+) by mitochondrial shuttles
